The cause of the fire was not yet known. Fire and Rescue spokesperson Theo Layne said the fire started at a residential dwelling in Sering Crescent. The fire claimed the life of the man just before 3am, while  firefighters battled to extinguish the blaze. A formal dwelling was gutted by the fire, and four wooden and iron structures were destroyed. The Cityâ€™s executive director for safety and security, Richard Bosman, confirmed that emergency relief was given to the family. Bosman said Fire and Rescue services responded to the fire at  2.13am and the fire was finally extinguished at 3.27am.